<p><a name="author"><span class="atitle">About the author</span></a></p><div class="ibm-container ibm-portrait-module ibm-alternate-two"><div class="ibm-container-body"><p><a name="author1"></a>A senior software engineer with more than 20 years of experience, Jack Herrington is the author of three books: <i>
                    <a href="http://www.codegeneration.net/cgia">Code Generation in Action</a>, <a href="http://www.oreilly.com/catalog/podcastinghks/">Podcasting Hacks</a>,</i> and <i>
                    <a href="http://www.oreilly.com/catalog/phphks/">PHP Hacks</a>.</i> He is also the author of more than 30 articles. You can contact him at <a href="mailto:jherr@pobox.com?cc=dwxed@us.ibm.com">jherr@pobox.com</a>.</p></div></div>
